Program: Outlook
Title: 09/07/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00tzmlp
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 10 Jul 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Syrian children speak about torture they've suffered at the hands of the army - we speak to the UN officer who heard their testimony. Also, Uganda's first wildlife vet on her work protecting gorillas and the humans who live near them. And the taste of Peru - an ex-pat living in London recalls the food that reminds her of home. Show less